{
  "texts": [
    "This approach employs a deep neural network, trained to predict specific molecular properties.",
    "By reversing the network and inputting desired property values, one can generate molecules optimized for those properties, an improvement over the more abstract latent space of VAEs.",
    "• Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs): This architecture involves two competing neural networks: a generator and a discriminator.",
    "The generator's primary objective is to create molecular structures that the discriminator cannot distinguish from genuine molecules.",
    "The first example in generative drug design was ORGANIC (66) and other ones were rapidly developed, such as ATNC (67) and MolGAN (68) which improved the rate of valid molecules generated."
  ]
}